{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2b7b3cca-c507-44f2-87ea-17995b1461ff","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Recursive wildcard glob (line 9 of `.csproj`) — **High impact**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThe `**\\*.*` glob forces MSBuild to walk the **entire directory tree** during evaluation. This is the single most expensive evaluation pattern, especially as the repo grows. Use a targeted path or specific extensions instead.\n\n### 2. File I/O via property function (line 13) — **Medium impact**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\n`File.ReadAllText` executes during **every evaluation pass** (design-time builds, restores, IDE reloads). Disk I/O in property functions blocks the evaluation thread. If you need file content, read it in a target at build time (inside a `<Target>`) instead.\n\n### 3. Three-level deep import chain — **Low-medium impact**\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach `<Import>` adds an XML parse + evaluation pass. The chain is only 3 deep here, but it adds up in larger solutions and makes evaluation harder to cache. Flatten where possible.\n\n### Summary of recommended fixes\n\n| Issue | Fix |\n|---|---|\n| `**\\*.*` glob | Scope to specific folder/extensions, e.g. `src\\**\\*.cs` |\n| `File::ReadAllText` in PropertyGroup | Move to a `<Target>` with `Inputs/Outputs` caching |\n| Nested imports | Consolidate into fewer files |\n\nThe recursive glob is the most critical — it scales with the file system and re-runs on every IDE evaluation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e2e71ba4-4386-4509-9c25-3697478d5ad1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.","outputTokens":490,"requestId":"7806:1F3FEB:8614524:9473B6C:69EAC563"},"id":"0221eb5d-2e9f-41eb-aa27-d0b386486309","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:20:51.718Z","parentId":"b0110cfd-77fd-4ed8-b465-8bf94787eeaa"}
